                        <foliation xml:id="original">Correctly foliated in <material>black</material>Hindu-Arabic numerals on the upper-left corners of the a sides, starting on folio <locus from="25a" to="139a">25a</locus>, followed for this record.</foliation>
                        <foliation xml:id="modern">Pencilled Arabic numerals confusingly commence with <locus from="2a" to="101a">2a to 101a</locus> then stop, hence off by one.</foliation>
                        <collation>Primarily quaternions throughout 17IV(136)1II+1(139). <catchwords>Catchwords throughout most of the lower-left corners of the b sides.</catchwords></collation>
                        <condition>In good condition.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" ruledLines="13" n="mistara">  Written in 1 column with 13 lines per page. Ruled with a <hi rend="italic">misṭarah</hi> hand guide.</layout>                  
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>                                   
                  <handDesc>
